Package remodel.io

Class ExpressionWriter

java.lang.Object
remodel.io.AbstractWriter
remodel.io.ExpressionWriter
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Closeable, java.lang.AutoCloseable, ExpressionVisitor, TokenCodes
Direct Known Subclasses:
MetamodelWriter, TransformWriter
public abstract class ExpressionWriter
extends AbstractWriter
implements ExpressionVisitor, TokenCodes
ExpressionWriter is the abstract ancestor of pretty-printers that format code expressions. The descendants of ExpressionWriter are MetamodelWriter and TransformWriter. ExpressionWriter sends its text output to a buffered ModelStreamer. ExpressionWriter fulfils the role of a visitor in the Visitor Design Pattern, by virtue of implementing the ExpressionVisitor interface. Expression nodes in the parse-tree are visited by this ExpressionWriter, and reciprocally invoke the appropriate writing method for the type of node.

ExpressionWriter implements the Closeable interface (by inheriting from AbstractWriter), so may be used in try-with-resources blocks, in order to ensure that the ExpressionWriter and all underlying input streams are closed safely.

Version:
1.0
Author:
Anthony J H Simons
